The paper deals with the optimization of communication in an ultra-dense cloud radio access network (UD-CRAN) with limited fronthaul capacity. This involves joint signal processing, user-SC assignments, and power allocation. The paper also proposes a hybrid decoding scheme to save fronthaul capacity. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Multimedia (cs.MM), and Computer Communications (cs.COM) sub-categories.
